1. Accept a single command-line argument, a non-negative integer.

2. If no command-line argument, or with more than one command-line argument,
it should print an error message and return 1 in the main function.

3. If the command-line argument is not a decimal number, it should print
Usage: ./caesar key, and return 1 in the main function.

4. it should prompt user to type the plaintext.

5. it should only encrypt the english alphabet, and remain the case.

6. it should output the cipertext by rotate k positions, after outputting ciphertext,
it should print a newline.


check the number of command-line argument is 1
If 1 (k)
    If decimal number
        prompt user to type plaintext
        loop all the character of the plaintext
            If English alphabet
                rotate k position
            ELSE
                no rotate
        end
        output cipertext

    ELSE
        error message (Usage: ./caesar key)
ELSE
    error message